extends layout

block content
  if email == true
    .modal#modal
      p Email was sent! Thanks for reaching out.
      button(id="close-modal") Close
  else if email == false
    .modal#modal
      p Email was not sent. Try again later
      button(id="close-modal") Close
  .welcome
    .hundred
      h1 i'm michael
      h2 i'm a web developer
      img#logo(src='images/logo.svg' alt='logo')
  .container
    .container-item
      #portfolio
        .portfolio-item#linode
          .icons
            a
              i(class="fab fa-ubuntu")
            a
              i(class="fab fa-linode")
            a
              i(class="fab fa-raspberry-pi")
            a
              i(class="fab fa-docker")
          .hundred
            a Linux / Linode / Rasberry Pi
          .hundred
            a(href="https://github.com/nishiguchi-michael/portfolio" class="git" target="_blank") Github Repository
              img(src="images/icons/git.png")
          p This website and all of the following projects are hosted on a Linode server running Ubuntu. I have also created a backup on a Rasberry Pi.
        .portfolio-item
          .icons
            a(href="https://food.michael-nishiguchi.com" target="_blank")
              i(class="fab fa-node")
            a(href="https://food.michael-nishiguchi.com" target="_blank")
              i(class="fas fa-database")
            a(href="https://food.michael-nishiguchi.com" target="_blank")
              i(class="fab fa-google")
          .hundred
            a(class="title" href="https://food.michael-nishiguchi.com" target="_blank") Food Tracker
          .hundred
            a(href="https://github.com/nishiguchi-michael/food-tracker" class="git" target="_blank") Github Repository
              img(src="images/icons/git.png")
          p This is a food tracker made using Node.JS, PostgresSQL, and Google's authentication API. I love tracking nutrition and wasn't happy with the available tools like My Fitness Pal or Lose It so I decided to make my own. I also got to learn how to make a website with a neumorphic user interface.

        .portfolio-item
          .icons
            a(href="https://planner.michael-nishiguchi.com" target="_blank")
              i(class="fab fa-windows")
              i(class="far fa-clipboard")
          .hundred
            a(href="https://planner.michael-nishiguchi.com" class="title" target="_blank") Schedule creation tool
          .hundred
            a(href="https://github.com/nishiguchi-michael/meeting-planner" class="git" target="_blank") Github Repository
              img(src="images/icons/git.png")
          p This is an ASP.NET application that can help people create church meeting schedules. It uses SqLite to manage the database.

        .portfolio-item
          .icons
            a(href='https://notes.michael-nishiguchi.com' target="_blank")
              i(class="fas fa-book")
          a(href='https://notes.michael-nishiguchi.com' target="_blank" class="title") Node JS Note Taking App
          .hundred
            a(href="https://github.com/nishiguchi-michael/note-app-pug" target="_blank" class="git") github repository
              img(src="images/icons/git.png")
          p Here's a notetaking app that uses NodeJS and Express. You can register for an account, log in/out and view/edit/delete notes for each account.

        .portfolio-item
          .icons
            a(href='https://michael-nishiguchi.com/nyt/index.html' target="_blank")
              i(class="far fa-newspaper")
          a(href='http://michael-nishiguchi.com/nyt/index.html' target="_blank" class="title") Somethin' Good
          .hundred
            a(href="https://github.com/nishiguchi-michael/nyt" target="_blank" class="git") github repository
              img(src="images/icons/git.png")
          p This was a fun project where I used the New York Times API to retrieve data. The application lets you search for articles and filter articles by topics you don&apos;t want to see.
